 first, that would be a splendid arrangement. But please, if possible, do not put me down for an hour earlier than 11.

We both wish you both a very happy New Year. I was delighted to hear of your receiving the "rosette".1

Sincerely yours,





TO: COL. JOSEPH I. GREENE1

CC, 1 p.

Cambridge, Mass.





January 14, 1948

